<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861203-0158 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News:Standard-Pacific Corp.</HL><DD> 12/03/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SPFDIVIDENDS (DIV) </IN><TEXT>   STANDARD-PACIFIC CORP. said it will make a special cash distribution of $3 a common share, payable before April 15 to stock of record shortly before that date. The Costa Mesa, Calif.-based home builder said the special distribution is intended to help shareholders pay federal income taxes resulting from the company's planned conversion to a limited partnership. The conversion is expected to occur before the end of the year, Standard-Pacific said. The company has about 11.6 million shares outstanding. </TEXT></DOC>